1 Further amend said bill, Page 76, Section 660.520, Line 40, by inserting after said section and
2 line the following:
3
4 "[650.058. 1. Notwithstanding the sovereign immunity of the state,
5 any individual who was found guilty of a felony in a Missouri court and was
6 later determined to be actually innocent of such crime may be paid restitution.
7 The individual may receive an amount of one hundred seventy-nine dollars per
8 day for each day of postconviction incarceration for the crime for which the
9 individual is determined to be actually innocent. The petition for the payment
10 of said restitution shall be filed with the sentencing court. For the purposes of
11 this section, the term "actually innocent" shall mean:
12 (1) The individual was convicted of a felony for which a final order of
13 release was entered by the court;
14 (2) All appeals of the order of release have been exhausted;
15 (3) The individual was not serving any term of a sentence for any other
16 crime concurrently with the sentence for which he or she is determined to be
17 actually innocent, unless such individual was serving another concurrent
18 sentence because his or her parole was revoked by a court or the parole board
19 in connection with the crime for which the person has been exonerated.
20 Regardless of whether any other basis may exist for the revocation of the
21 person's probation or parole at the time of conviction for the crime for which
22 the person is later determined to be actually innocent, when the court's or the
23 parole board's sole stated reason for the revocation in its order is the conviction
24 for the crime for which the person is later determined to be actually innocent,
25 such order shall, for purposes of this section only, be conclusive evidence that
26 the persons's probation or parole was revoked in connection with the crime for
27 which the person has been exonerated; and
28 (4) Testing ordered under section 547.035, or testing by the order of
29 any state or federal court, if such person was exonerated on or before August
30 28, 2004, or testing ordered under section 650.055, if such person was or is
31 exonerated after August 28, 2004, or after an evidentiary hearing and finding in
32 a habeas corpus proceeding or a proceeding held pursuant to section 547.031
33 which demonstrates a person's innocence of the crime for which the person is
34 in custody.
35
36 Any individual who receives restitution under this section shall be prohibited
37 from seeking any civil redress from the state, its departments and agencies, or
38 any employee thereof, or any political subdivision or its employees. This
39 section shall not be construed as a waiver of sovereign immunity for any
40 purposes other than the restitution provided for herein. The department of
41 corrections shall determine the aggregate amount of restitution owed during a
42 fiscal year. If insufficient moneys are appropriated each fiscal year to pay
43 restitution to such persons, the department shall pay each individual who has
44 received an order awarding restitution a pro rata share of the amount
45 appropriated. Provided sufficient moneys are appropriated to the department,
Page 11 of 12

5011H04.01H
1 the amounts owed to such individual shall be paid on June thirtieth of each
2 subsequent fiscal year, until such time as the restitution to the individual has
3 been paid in full. However, no individual awarded restitution under this
4 subsection shall receive more than sixty-five thousand dollars during each
5 fiscal year. No interest on unpaid restitution shall be awarded to the individual.
6 However, an individual may also be awarded other nonmonetary relief,
7 including counseling, housing assistance, and personal financial literary
8 assistance.
9 2. If the results of the DNA testing confirm the person's guilt, then the
10 person filing for DNA testing under section 547.035, shall:
11 (1) Be liable for any reasonable costs incurred when conducting the
12 DNA test, including but not limited to the cost of the test. Such costs shall be
13 determined by the court and shall be included in the findings of fact and
14 conclusions of law made by the court; and
15 (2) Be sanctioned under the provisions of section 217.262.
16 3. A petition for payment of restitution under this section may be filed
17 only by the individual determined to be actually innocent or the individual's
18 legal guardian. No claim or petition for restitution under this section may be
19 filed by the individual's heirs or assigns. An individual's right to receive
20 restitution under this section is not assignable or otherwise transferrable. The
21 state's obligation to pay restitution under this section shall cease upon the
22 individual's death. Any beneficiary designation that purports to bequeath,
23 assign, or otherwise convey the right to receive such restitution shall be void
24 and unenforceable.
25 4. An individual who is determined to be actually innocent of a crime
26 under this chapter shall automatically be granted an order of expungement
27 from the court in which he or she pled guilty or was sentenced to expunge from
28 all official records all recordations of his or her arrest, plea, trial or conviction.
29 Upon the court's granting of the order of expungement, the records and files
30 maintained in any administrative or court proceeding in an associate or circuit
31 division of the court shall be confidential and available only to the parties or by
32 order of the court for good cause shown. The effect of such order shall be to
33 restore such person to the status he or she occupied prior to such arrest, plea or
34 conviction and as if such event had never taken place. No person as to whom
35 such order has been entered shall be held thereafter under any provision of any
36 law to be guilty of perjury or otherwise giving a false statement by reason of
37 his or her failure to recite or acknowledge such arrest, plea, trial, conviction or
38 expungement in response to any inquiry made of him or her for any purpose
39 whatsoever and no such inquiry shall be made for information relating to an
40 expungement under this section.]"; and
41
42 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
43 accordingly.
